<paragraph id="25262F0E1037FFA8DBB2F99F4D4F2DC3" blockId="18.[151,468,1711,1774]" box="[151,378,1748,1774]" pageId="18" pageNumber="119">
(
<figureCitation id="BDA2338B1037FFA8DBBAF99F4D2A2DC3" box="[159,287,1748,1774]" captionStart="FIGURES 11–22" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1805,1829]" captionTargetBox="[158,1424,181,1782]" captionTargetId="figure-17@5.[158,1430,181,1782]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 11–22. Asianthrips species. A. magnus, 11–12; (11) Female (mac); (12) Female (mic). A. malayanus, 13–14; (13), Female (mac); (14) Non-paratypic female (mic). A. nobilis, 15–16; (15) Female (mac); (16) Female (mic). A. orientalis, 17–18; (17) Female (mac); (18) Male (mic). A. pallens, 19–20; (19) Female (mac); (20) Male (mic). A. parvinotus, 21–22; (21) Female (mac); (22) Male, non-paratype (mic)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6404870" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6404870/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="119">Figs 11–12</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="BDA2338B1037FFA8DA0EF99F4D462DC3" box="[299,371,1748,1774]" captionStart="FIGURES 80–87" captionStartId="19.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[226,1361,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-17@19.[226,1361,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURES 80–87. Asianthrips magnus, sp. n., female. (80) Head (mac); (81) Head (mic); (82) Antenna (mac); (83) Metanotum (mac); (84) Metanotum &amp; pelta (mic); (85) Mesopresternum (mac); (86) Pelta (mac); (87) Tube (mac)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6404902" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6404902/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="119">80–87</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="25262F0E1037FFAEDBB2F8574E102910" blockId="18.[151,1437,1820,2026]" lastBlockId="20.[151,1437,151,1293]" lastPageId="20" lastPageNumber="121" pageId="18" pageNumber="119">
<emphasis id="17EDF31C1037FFA8DBB2F8574D4C2C1B" box="[151,377,1820,1846]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="119">Female macroptera</emphasis>
. 
<materialsCitation id="95F125531037FFAEDAAEF8574E142910" ID-GBIF-Occurrence="3744622317" collectionCode="III, VII, VIII, V" lastPageId="20" lastPageNumber="121" pageId="18" pageNumber="119" specimenCount="4" typeStatus="holotype">
Body brown (
<figureCitation id="BDA2338B1037FFA8D90AF8574EB02C1B" box="[559,645,1820,1846]" captionStart="FIGURES 11–22" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1805,1829]" captionTargetBox="[158,1424,181,1782]" captionTargetId="figure-17@5.[158,1430,181,1782]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 11–22. Asianthrips species. A. magnus, 11–12; (11) Female (mac); (12) Female (mic). A. malayanus, 13–14; (13), Female (mac); (14) Non-paratypic female (mic). A. nobilis, 15–16; (15) Female (mac); (16) Female (mic). A. orientalis, 17–18; (17) Female (mac); (18) Male (mic). A. pallens, 19–20; (19) Female (mac); (20) Male (mic). A. parvinotus, 21–22; (21) Female (mac); (22) Male, non-paratype (mic)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6404870" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6404870/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="119">Fig. 11</figureCitation>
). Antennal segment 
<collectionCode id="4388B7CB1037FFA8D85DF8574FA12C1B" box="[888,916,1820,1846]" pageId="18" pageNumber="119">III</collectionCode>
yellow, distal half shaded with pale brown; remaining segments uniformly brown. All femora brown, concolourous with body, with extreme apices yellowish; all tibiae and tarsi yellow. Fore wings very weakly shaded with brown at basal half. Body setae almost colourless. Head (
<figureCitation id="BDA2338B1037FFA8DBC7F8C34D012C8F" box="[226,308,1928,1954]" captionStart="FIGURES 80–87" captionStartId="19.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[226,1361,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-17@19.[226,1361,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURES 80–87. Asianthrips magnus, sp. n., female. (80) Head (mac); (81) Head (mic); (82) Antenna (mac); (83) Metanotum (mac); (84) Metanotum &amp; pelta (mic); (85) Mesopresternum (mac); (86) Pelta (mac); (87) Tube (mac)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6404902" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6404902/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="119">Fig. 80</figureCitation>
) longer than wide, 1.16 times as long as wide in 
<typeStatus id="FA2291AC1037FFA8D87AF8C34FF02C8F" box="[863,965,1928,1954]" pageId="18" pageNumber="119">holotype</typeStatus>
; dorsal surface sculptured with transverse reticulation, but the reticles very weak or almost smooth between eyes; ocellar region weakly protruded to a cone at an acute angle. Cheeks very weakly rounded, weakly narrowed to base. Postocular setae almost as long as eyes. Postocellar setae weakly developed, shorter than a diameter of posterior ocellus. Eyes well developed, 0.37 times as long as head in 
<typeStatus id="FA2291AC1031FFAEDA61FFF04D9F2BF8" box="[324,426,187,213]" pageId="20" pageNumber="121">holotype</typeStatus>
. Antennal segments 
<collectionCode id="4388B7CB1031FFAED9A8FFF04E812BF8" box="[653,692,187,213]" pageId="20" pageNumber="121">VII</collectionCode>
and 
<collectionCode id="4388B7CB1031FFAED9CDFFF04F2D2BF8" box="[744,792,187,213]" pageId="20" pageNumber="121">VIII</collectionCode>
somewhat broadly fused, but 
<collectionCode id="4388B7CB1031FFAEDF43FFF048A32BF8" box="[1126,1174,187,213]" pageId="20" pageNumber="121">VIII</collectionCode>
not constricted basally, cone-shaped (
<figureCitation id="BDA2338B1031FFAEDA16FF944DBD2BD4" box="[307,392,223,249]" captionStart="FIGURES 80–87" captionStartId="19.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[226,1361,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-17@19.[226,1361,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURES 80–87. Asianthrips magnus, sp. n., female. (80) Head (mac); (81) Head (mic); (82) Antenna (mac); (83) Metanotum (mac); (84) Metanotum &amp; pelta (mic); (85) Mesopresternum (mac); (86) Pelta (mac); (87) Tube (mac)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6404902" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6404902/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="121">Fig. 82</figureCitation>
); segment 
<collectionCode id="4388B7CB1031FFAED924FF944E282BD4" box="[513,541,223,249]" pageId="20" pageNumber="121">III</collectionCode>
with three sense cones. Maxillary stylets retracted into 2/5 of head capsule, but not reaching postocular setae, rather wide apart, a little wider than 1/3 of the head width apart at the basal collar of head. Pronotum 0.53 times as long as head and 2.17 times as wide as long in 
<typeStatus id="FA2291AC1031FFAEDF39FE6C48B72A6C" box="[1052,1154,295,321]" pageId="20" pageNumber="121">holotype</typeStatus>
; pa about 2/3 the median pronotal length. Metanotum (
<figureCitation id="BDA2338B1031FFAEDAC1FE004E032A48" box="[484,566,331,357]" captionStart="FIGURES 80–87" captionStartId="19.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[226,1361,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-17@19.[226,1361,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURES 80–87. Asianthrips magnus, sp. n., female. (80) Head (mac); (81) Head (mic); (82) Antenna (mac); (83) Metanotum (mac); (84) Metanotum &amp; pelta (mic); (85) Mesopresternum (mac); (86) Pelta (mac); (87) Tube (mac)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6404902" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6404902/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="121">Fig. 83</figureCitation>
) polygonally reticulated anteriorly, longitudinally reticulated posteriorly, but very weak. Prospinasternum largely developed. Mesopresternum and mesoeusternum (
<figureCitation id="BDA2338B1031FFAEDFA3FE2448EE2AA4" box="[1158,1243,366,393]" captionStart="FIGURES 80–87" captionStartId="19.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[226,1361,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-17@19.[226,1361,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURES 80–87. Asianthrips magnus, sp. n., female. (80) Head (mac); (81) Head (mic); (82) Antenna (mac); (83) Metanotum (mac); (84) Metanotum &amp; pelta (mic); (85) Mesopresternum (mac); (86) Pelta (mac); (87) Tube (mac)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6404902" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6404902/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="121">Fig. 85</figureCitation>
) narrowly fused medially, with long sutures between them at both sides; mesopresternum eroded medially. Fore tarsi unarmed. Fore wings with 6–8 duplicated cilia in 
<typeStatus id="FA2291AC1031FFAED933FEFC4E492AFC" box="[534,636,439,465]" pageId="20" pageNumber="121">holotype</typeStatus>
. Pelta irregular trapezoid (
<figureCitation id="BDA2338B1031FFAED884FEFC4FC62AFF" box="[929,1011,439,466]" captionStart="FIGURES 80–87" captionStartId="19.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[226,1361,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-17@19.[226,1361,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURES 80–87. Asianthrips magnus, sp. n., female. (80) Head (mac); (81) Head (mic); (82) Antenna (mac); (83) Metanotum (mac); (84) Metanotum &amp; pelta (mic); (85) Mesopresternum (mac); (86) Pelta (mac); (87) Tube (mac)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6404902" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6404902/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="121">Fig. 86</figureCitation>
), very weakly reticulated. Tergites not small, tergites 
<collectionCode id="4388B7CB1031FFAEDA1CFE904D602AD8" box="[313,341,475,501]" pageId="20" pageNumber="121">III</collectionCode>
– 
<collectionCode id="4388B7CB1031FFAEDA46FE904D422AD8" box="[355,375,475,501]" country="Canada" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:13946" name="Royal British Columbia Museum - Herbarium" pageId="20" pageNumber="121" type="Museum">V</collectionCode>
much wider than pronotum. S1 setae on tergite IX a little longer than S2, about 2/3 the length of tube, S1 weakly expanded, S2 very blunt or nearly pointed at apex. Tube (
<figureCitation id="BDA2338B1031FFAED8F3FEB4481D2934" box="[982,1064,511,537]" captionStart="FIGURES 80–87" captionStartId="19.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[226,1361,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-17@19.[226,1361,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURES 80–87. Asianthrips magnus, sp. n., female. (80) Head (mac); (81) Head (mic); (82) Antenna (mac); (83) Metanotum (mac); (84) Metanotum &amp; pelta (mic); (85) Mesopresternum (mac); (86) Pelta (mac); (87) Tube (mac)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6404902" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6404902/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="121">Fig. 87</figureCitation>
) about 0.6 times as long as head. Anal setae a little shorter than tube
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<caption id="71E67F861036FFA9DBB2F8DC489D2CF9" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6404902" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6404902" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6404902/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="120" startId="19.[151,264,1943,1967]" targetBox="[226,1361,181,1919]" targetPageId="19">
<paragraph id="25262F0E1036FFA9DBB2F8DC489D2CF9" blockId="19.[151,1436,1943,2004]" pageId="19" pageNumber="120">
<emphasis id="17EDF31C1036FFA9DBB2F8DC4D612C82" bold="true" box="[151,340,1943,1967]" pageId="19" pageNumber="120">FIGURES 80–87.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="E299548D1036FFA9DA7CF8D34E172C82" authority="Okajima &amp; Masumoto, 2022" authorityName="Okajima &amp; Masumoto" authorityYear="2022" box="[345,546,1944,1968]" class="Insecta" family="Phlaeothripidae" genus="Asianthrips" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="120" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="magnus" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis id="17EDF31C1036FFA9DA7CF8D34E172C82" box="[345,546,1944,1968]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="120">Asianthrips magnus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<emphasis id="17EDF31C1036FFA9D90BF8D34E522C9D" bold="true" box="[558,615,1944,1968]" pageId="19" pageNumber="120">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="0CDE4E671036FFA9D90BF8D34E522C9D" box="[558,615,1944,1968]" pageId="19" pageNumber="120" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, female. (80) Head (mac); (81) Head (mic); (82) Antenna (mac); (83) Metanotum (mac); (84) Metanotum &amp; pelta (mic); (85) Mesopresternum (mac); (86) Pelta (mac); (87) Tube (mac).
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="25262F0E1031FFAEDBE2FD0C4CFD2838" blockId="20.[151,1437,151,1293]" pageId="20" pageNumber="121">
<emphasis id="17EDF31C1031FFAEDBE2FD0C4D43294C" bold="true" box="[199,374,583,609]" pageId="20" pageNumber="121">Measurements</emphasis>
. Female 
<typeStatus id="FA2291AC1031FFAEDAC0FD0C4E72294C" box="[485,583,583,609]" pageId="20" pageNumber="121">holotype</typeStatus>
(mac.) in microns. Distended body length about 2000. Head length 189, width across cheeks 163. Compound eye dorsal length about 70. Pronotum length 100, width 217. Fore wing length about 860. Tube length 117, width across base 56. Antenna length about 400, segments III–VIII length (width) as follows: 60 (30), 63 (30), 55 (26), 53 (23), 48 (20), 32 (13). Postocular setae 68–72. Pronotal aa 50–53, am 47–48, ml 57–58, pa 65–68, epim about 70. S1 setae on tergite IX 78–79, S2 setae on tergite IX 66–73. Anal setae about 100.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="25262F0E1031FFAEDBE2FC544D1328E4" blockId="20.[151,1437,151,1293]" pageId="20" pageNumber="121">
<emphasis id="17EDF31C1031FFAEDBE2FC544D962815" box="[199,419,799,825]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="121">Female microptera.</emphasis>
Colour very similar to macropterous female (
<figureCitation id="BDA2338B1031FFAED8B3FC544FD32814" box="[918,998,799,825]" captionStart="FIGURES 11–22" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1805,1829]" captionTargetBox="[158,1424,181,1782]" captionTargetId="figure-17@5.[158,1430,181,1782]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 11–22. Asianthrips species. A. magnus, 11–12; (11) Female (mac); (12) Female (mic). A. malayanus, 13–14; (13), Female (mac); (14) Non-paratypic female (mic). A. nobilis, 15–16; (15) Female (mac); (16) Female (mic). A. orientalis, 17–18; (17) Female (mac); (18) Male (mic). A. pallens, 19–20; (19) Female (mac); (20) Male (mic). A. parvinotus, 21–22; (21) Female (mac); (22) Male, non-paratype (mic)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6404870" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6404870/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="121">Fig. 12</figureCitation>
), but anterior portion of head somewhat yellowish. Eyes small (
<figureCitation id="BDA2338B1031FFAEDAB2FC084DDD2870" box="[407,488,835,861]" captionStart="FIGURES 80–87" captionStartId="19.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[226,1361,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-17@19.[226,1361,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURES 80–87. Asianthrips magnus, sp. n., female. (80) Head (mac); (81) Head (mic); (82) Antenna (mac); (83) Metanotum (mac); (84) Metanotum &amp; pelta (mic); (85) Mesopresternum (mac); (86) Pelta (mac); (87) Tube (mac)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6404902" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6404902/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="121">Fig. 81</figureCitation>
), 0.30–0.32 times as long as head. Maxillary stylets retracted into 1/2 of head capsule, almost reaching postocular setae. Pronotum 0.64–0.66 times as long as head. Posterior half of metanotum almost smooth (
<figureCitation id="BDA2338B1031FFAEDBDCFCC04D7B2888" box="[249,334,907,933]" captionStart="FIGURES 80–87" captionStartId="19.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[226,1361,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-17@19.[226,1361,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURES 80–87. Asianthrips magnus, sp. n., female. (80) Head (mac); (81) Head (mic); (82) Antenna (mac); (83) Metanotum (mac); (84) Metanotum &amp; pelta (mic); (85) Mesopresternum (mac); (86) Pelta (mac); (87) Tube (mac)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6404902" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6404902/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="121">Fig. 84</figureCitation>
). Pelta (
<figureCitation id="BDA2338B1031FFAEDA8FFCC04DC92888" box="[426,508,907,933]" captionStart="FIGURES 80–87" captionStartId="19.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[226,1361,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-17@19.[226,1361,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURES 80–87. Asianthrips magnus, sp. n., female. (80) Head (mac); (81) Head (mic); (82) Antenna (mac); (83) Metanotum (mac); (84) Metanotum &amp; pelta (mic); (85) Mesopresternum (mac); (86) Pelta (mac); (87) Tube (mac)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6404902" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6404902/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="121">Fig. 84</figureCitation>
) much wider than long. Sigmoid wing retaining setae absent. Anal setae almost as long as tube.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="25262F0E1031FFAEDBE2FC9848922F50" blockId="20.[151,1437,151,1293]" pageId="20" pageNumber="121">
<emphasis id="17EDF31C1031FFAEDBE2FC984D4328C0" bold="true" box="[199,374,979,1005]" pageId="20" pageNumber="121">Measurements</emphasis>
. Female 
<typeStatus id="FA2291AC1031FFAEDAF9FC984E0928C0" box="[476,572,979,1005]" pageId="20" pageNumber="121">paratype</typeStatus>
(mic.) in microns. Distended body length about 1900. Head length 175, width across cheeks 158. Compound eye dorsal length 53–55. Pronotum length 112, width 237. Fore wing length?. Tube length 108, width across base 59. Antenna length about 390, segments III–VIII length (width) as follows: 57 (28), 63 (30), 52 (26), 51 (25), 45 (20), 32 (13). Postocular setae 75–76. Pronotal aa 41–42, am 43–43, ml 57–73, pa 62–67, epim 63–70. S1 setae on tergite IX 80–85, S2 setae on tergite IX 65–75. Anal setae 112–113.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
