<emphasis id="17EDF31C1031FFAEDBE2FB844D012FC4" bold="true" box="[199,308,1231,1257]" pageId="20" pageNumber="121">Remarks</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName id="E299548D1031FFAEDA67FB844D8C2FC5" authorityName="Okajima &amp; Masumoto" authorityYear="2022" box="[322,441,1231,1257]" class="Insecta" family="Phlaeothripidae" genus="Asianthrips" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="121" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="magnus">
<emphasis id="17EDF31C1031FFAEDA67FB844D8C2FC5" box="[322,441,1231,1257]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="121">A. magnus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is unique in having the head with very weak sculpture between the eyes, and the ocellar region that is weakly protruded at an acute angle as a cone (
<figureCitation id="BDA2338B1031FFAED811FBB84FFE2E20" box="[820,971,1267,1293]" captionStart="FIGURES 80–87" captionStartId="19.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[226,1361,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-17@19.[226,1361,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURES 80–87. Asianthrips magnus, sp. n., female. (80) Head (mac); (81) Head (mic); (82) Antenna (mac); (83) Metanotum (mac); (84) Metanotum &amp; pelta (mic); (85) Mesopresternum (mac); (86) Pelta (mac); (87) Tube (mac)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6404902" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6404902/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="121">Figs 80 &amp; 81</figureCitation>
